{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Operations Guide{% endblock %}

{% block pageContent %}
<div class="min-h-[80vh] overflow-hidden">
    <div class="relative isolate overflow-hidden rounded-3xl bg-gradient-to-br from-slate-900 via-emerald-900/30 to-cyan-800/20 p-10 shadow-xl mb-10">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-30" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="absolute -left-10 -top-10 h-64 w-64 rounded-full bg-cyan-500 blur-3xl"></div>
            <div class="absolute bottom-0 right-0 h-72 w-72 rounded-full bg-indigo-500 blur-3xl"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="relative space-y-4 max-w-4xl">
            <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-cyan-200/80 flex items-center gap-2">
                <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" class="size-5 opacity-80">
                    <path d="M3 12h18"></path>
                    <path d="M8 7l-2 5 2 5"></path>
                    <path d="M16 7l2 5-2 5"></path>
                    <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"></circle>
                </svg>
                Operations Checklist
            </p>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight">Spin up the bridge, fuel the ledger.</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-slate-200/90">Follow this flight plan to light up a Traveller campaign: campaign clock, hulls, crews, counterparties, costs, incomes, mortgages, and the annual budget strip.</p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-200/70">
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Campaign first</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Shipyard & Crew</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Costs & Income</span>
                <span class="badge badge-outline badge-sm">Mortgage & Budget</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 1</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Spin up the Campaign</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Name the op, drop a short brief, and set the session calendar (day/year). Keep the session date updated as in-game time advances: every downstream date (mortgage, PDFs, forms) syncs to this clock.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 2</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Register the Ships</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Drop in hulls for PCs or NPCs. Give them class/type, price, and details if needed. NPC ships can sail without mortgages, costs, or income if they’re just scenery in your sector.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 3</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Set up Companies</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Add counterparties with roles and sign labels. They sign mortgages, show up on costs/income as vendors or patrons, and bring their local law/disclaimer baggage.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 4</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Dock ships to the Campaign</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Link each hull to the campaign so every date tracks the same session clock. Session day/year will drive ship PDFs, mortgages, and contracts automatically.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 5</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Crew up</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Add crew, assign bridge roles, and tether people to their ships. Flag the captain, keep roles consistent with ship operations, and ensure your crew roster mirrors the fiction.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 6</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Log the Costs</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Record costs per ship and category, add line-item details and payment date. Keep company/local law aligned so PDFs carry the right jurisdiction and disclaimers.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 7</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Log the Income</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">Add income per ship and category (Freight, Contract, etc.) with dedicated details and printable PDFs. Signing date/location and local law keep contracts coherent with the table’s timeline.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 8</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Set up Mortgages</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">For financed hulls: set rate, insurance, installments; sign with session date + location; print the PDF (draft or signed). Unsign if needed to renegotiate before docking with the bank.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="rounded-2xl border border-white/10 bg-base-200/80 p-6 shadow-sm">
            <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-cyan-400 mb-2">Step 9</p>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-100">Build the Annual Budget</h3>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-300 mt-2">For each hull: aggregate income, costs, and installments in the current year and read the balance strip + timeline. Use it to plan the next jump or spot when debt will bite.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
{% endblock %}
